    "headline": "Molina Healthcare (NYSE:MOH) Posts Q2 CY2026 Sales In Line With Estimates But Stock Drops On Weak Guidance",
    "summary": "Healthcare insurance company Molina Healthcare (NYSE:MOH) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2026, but sales fell by 4.8% year on year to $10.87 billion. On the other hand, the company’s full-year revenue guidance of $42 billion at the midpoint came in 5.1% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.51 per share was 7.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.",
